<subSubSection pageId="101" pageNumber="859" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="101.[120,1327,3127,3478]" pageId="101" pageNumber="859">
Normally considered part of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Allen" authorityYear="1866" box="[614,749,3198,3231]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Rhogeessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="101" pageNumber="859" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tumida">R. tumida</taxonomicName>
complex, but recent molecular studies based on mtDNA and using nDNA markers found that this species and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LaVal" authorityYear="1973" box="[1149,1248,3237,3270]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Rhogeessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="101" pageNumber="859" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mira">R. mira</taxonomicName>
form a sister clade to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Allen" authorityYear="1866" box="[403,493,3277,3310]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Rhogeessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="101" pageNumber="859" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tumida">tumida</taxonomicName>
complex; this similarity between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Allen" authorityYear="1866" box="[963,1103,3277,3310]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Rhogeessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="101" pageNumber="859" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parvula">R. parvula</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LaVal" authorityYear="1973" box="[1174,1272,3277,3310]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Rhogeessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="101" pageNumber="859" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mira">R. mira</taxonomicName>
was also observed in external and skull morphology. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
